h3. Issue Summary

The *Code Snippet* macro is the best way to work with programming languages on Confluence. Sometimes our codes are too bigger, and this is expected depending on how our algorithm works or how much information the logs we are pasting there have.
 When the *Code Snippet* macro contains a huge amount of lines (around 3,500 or more), sometimes we will face performance issues when changing the page and publishing it and even errors.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new page on Confluence;
 # Call the *Code Snippet* macro;
 # Using [this text generator tool|https://www.handcoded.co.uk/php/app-1/], generate a text with 1,000 lines and copy it;
 # Paste it 4 times in the code snippet macro;
 # Publish the page (note it will take some time to get published);
 # Edit the page;
 # Insert some random text within the macro;
 # Publish the page.

h3. Expected Results

The page gets published with no apparent issue.
h3. Actual Results

The following behaviors happen:
 * The page takes some time to get published;
 * Eventually, it takes too much time and pops-up with the error {{There was an error processing the request}}
{{!image-2020-06-23-11-11-42-745.png|width=408,height=66!}}

h3. Workaround

In most of the cases, refreshing the page and publishing it will get the page published.

h3. Problem
The [Refined Toolkit for Confluence Cloud|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/apps/1216056/refined-toolkit-for-confluence-cloud?hosting=cloud&tab=overview] is an add-on developed and supported by our partner [Refined|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/vendors/15228/refined] and it is a cool option when we are talking about adding a different layout to our spaces.
There is a feature in this add-on that allows us to add a search bar on the overview page. When our space is open for anonymous access, this search used to work, but now, after a minute or so, it stops to work.

h3. Environment
Cloud

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Install the add-on [Refined Toolkit for Confluence Cloud|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/apps/1216056/refined-toolkit-for-confluence-cloud?hosting=cloud&tab=overview];
# Make sure your site is open for anonymous access;
# Go to a space and grant anonymous users with *view* permission;
# On this same space, go to *Space Settings > Look and Feel* and select the add-on to add a theme on your space;
# Go to the overview page and edit it;
# Add the search feature and publish the page;
# Using an incognito/inPrivate session of your browser, access the overview page of this space;
# Try to search for a page in the space (it shows some results);
# Wait a minute or so and try to search it again.

h3. Expected Results
The same results you received before appear.

h3. Actual Results
You receive the message {{The query could not be parsed}}

h3. Workaround
Currently, there is no workaround to be applied on this bug.

h3. Notes
In the network tab of the browser, it is possible to see a 403 request when you start receiving this message, with a response {{com.atlassian.confluence.api.service.exceptions.PermissionException: User not permitted to view user profiles}}

h3. Issue Summary

The [copy single page|#api-api-content-id-copy-post] REST API returns authorization errors when called with JWT and OAuth credentials.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Step 1: Invoke the copy single page API using any supported method: 3LO, JWT or AP.request. See code snippets:

Forge code snippet:

 
{code:java}
    const destinationType = 'existing_page';
    const targetContentId = 'etc';
    const bodyData = {
      copyAttachments: false,
      copyPermissions: false,
      copyProperties: false,
      copyLabels: true,
      copyCustomContents: false,
      destination: {
        type: destinationType,
        value: targetContentId
      },
      pageTitle: 'Copied Page'
    };
    const res = await api
      .asUser()
      .requestConfluence(`/wiki/rest/api/content/${contentId}/copy`, {          
        method: 'POST',
        body: JSON.stringify(bodyData)
      });
{code}
Connect ACJS code snippet:
{code:java}
const fromContentId = '179863892';
const destinationType = 'parent_page';
const targetContentId = '179699841';
const copyPageUrl = `/rest/api/content/${fromContentId}/copy`;
const data = {
  copyAttachments: false,
  copyPermissions: false,
  copyProperties: false,
  copyLabels: true,
  copyCustomContents: false,
  destination: {
    type: destinationType,
    value: targetContentId
  },
  pageTitle: 'Copied Page'
};
AP.request({
  url: copyPageUrl,
  type: 'POST',
  data: JSON.stringify(data),
  contentType: 'application/json',
  success: function(responseText) {
    console.log(responseText);
  },
  error: function(xhr, statusText, errorThrown) {
    console.log(statusText);
    console.log(errorThrown);
  }});   
{code}
 
h3. Expected Results

The API allows the request if the requesting user has the appropriate permissions and scopes.
h3. Actual Results

An error is returned. When invoking with 3LO credentials, the response is 401, but otherwise it is a 403.
h3. Workaround

None
